  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable</strong> <strong>oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>diced</strong> <strong>chicken breast</strong> and cook for 6 min or until golden</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-copy-1630489100040-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-copy-1630489100040-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-copy-1630489100040-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-copy-1630489100040-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-copy-1630489100040-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the chicken is cooking, heat a separate large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of<strong> vegetable</strong> <strong>oil</strong> over high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>rainbow</strong> <strong>veg mix </strong>and cook for 3 min or until the veg has slightly softened but still has some crunch</p><p>Once the veg has slightly softened, add the <strong>ginger & garlic paste </strong>and the <strong>edamame & jasmine rice</strong> and cook for a further 2-3 min or until fragrant</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-copy-1630489206186-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-copy-1630489206186-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-copy-1630489206186-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-copy-1630489206186-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-copy-1630489206186-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, combine the <strong>honey</strong>,<strong> tamari</strong>, <strong>sriracha </strong>and<strong> chilli flakes</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) in a small bowl<strong> </strong>– this is your <strong>spicy sauce</strong></p><p>Once the chicken is golden, transfer it to the rice pan and add the <strong>spicy sauce </strong>(reserve the pan!)</p><p>Give everything a good mix up and cook for 3 min further or until the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!) and everything is piping hot – this is your <strong>chicken nasi-goreng</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-copy-1630489216549-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-copy-1630489216549-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-copy-1630489216549-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-copy-1630489216549-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-copy-1630489216549-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pan to a medium-low heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, crack the <strong>eggs</strong> into the pan</p><p>Cover with a lid and cook for 2-3 min or until done to your liking</p><p>Tip: Shake your eggs before cracking for a perfectly-centred yolk</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-copy-1630489261362-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-copy-1630489261362-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-copy-1630489261362-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-copy-1630489261362-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-copy-1630489261362-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>chicken nasi-goreng</strong> topped with a <strong>fried egg </strong>and season with a generous pinch of<strong> salt </strong>and<strong> pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 5,
